1. Awareness of Existing Structure

Cursor must inspect the current project layout before generating code:

/src/components for stateful & domain-level components

/src/components/ui for shared presentational components

/src/pages for route-based pages

/src/styles for global style files and variables

Always search for existing modules or patterns to integrate with.

2. Component Reuse

Favor composition over duplication:

Identify existing UI components (e.g., Button, Card, Input) and import rather than recreate.

Extend or wrap existing components when customizing behavior or styles.

When introducing a new pattern, extract it into a reusable component in /src/components/ui.

3. Directory Organization

Adhere to the following folder structure:

/components (feature-specific / stateful)

/components/ui (generic, reusable presentational components)

/hooks (custom React hooks)

/utils (helper functions and constants)

/styles (global CSS, theming variables, CSS modules)

Place new files in the most semantically appropriate location.

4. Centralized Styling

Keep global styles and design tokens in styles/global.css or CSS modules under /styles.

Use CSS variables for colors, spacing, typography, and themes.

Avoid scattered inline styles; prefer class-based styling or CSS-in-JS following project conventions.

5. Theming: Light & Dark Mode

Maintain theme variables in styles/themes.css or global.css:

:root.light { --color-bg: #ffffff; --color-text: #000000; }
:root.dark  { --color-bg: #121212; --color-text: #ffffff; }

Generated components must reference theme variables (e.g., bg-[var(--color-bg)], text-[var(--color-text)]).

Use Tailwind’s dark: variants when applicable.

6. Naming Conventions

Components: PascalCase (e.g., UserProfile.js).

Hooks: useCamelCase (e.g., useFetchData.js).

Utilities: camelCase (e.g., formatDate.js).

Files: Match the exported entity (e.g., Button.js, button.module.css).

7. Code Generation Rules

Duplication Check: Before creating a new component, search existing codebase for similar functionality:

If found, prompt to reuse or extend.

If not, scaffold new component with boilerplate, tests, and Storybook story.

Scaffolding: Generate:

Component file (.js)

CSS module or styled file



